The paper deals with image segmentation, which is a core problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves registering a 3D model over the given image, which requires optimization techniques commonly used in robotics (cs.RO). The method also involves using level-set based segmentation, which is a popular technique in graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM). The use of a gradient-based loss function for registration suggests the use of machine learning techniques (cs.AI) in the proposed method.
